  "prompt": "What should I do if I lost my Chase debit card?",
  "response": "If you've lost your Chase debit card, here are the steps you should take:\n\n1. **Report the Loss**: Immediately report your lost debit card to Chase. You can do this through:\n   - The Chase mobile app\n   - The Chase website by logging into your account\n   - Calling the customer service number on the back of your card (if available) or their general support number at 1-800-935-9935.\n\n2. **Monitor Your Account**: Check your recent transactions for any unauthorized purchases. If you spot anything suspicious, report it to Chase right away.\n\n3. **Freeze Your Card**: If you're using the Chase mobile app or website, you can temporarily freeze your card to prevent any unauthorized use until you resolve the situation.\n\n4. **Request a Replacement Card**: After reporting the card lost, you can request a replacement through the same channels (mobile app, website, or phone).\n\n5. **Update Automatic Payments**: If you have automatic payments linked to your old card, remember to update them with your new card information once you receive it.\n\n6. **Change Your PIN**: As a precaution, consider changing your PIN associated with your debit card once you get your new card.\n\n7. **Stay Vigilant**: Keep monitoring your account statements regularly for any unusual activity.\n\nBy taking these steps promptly, you can help protect your finances and minimize any potential fraud.",
